   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "I haven't written a test for this, but it seems that a peer can fingerprint a chunk of our mempool by announcing a new compact block with a valid header, but inserting many `shorttxids` that don't belong to the block but are suspected to be in our mempool. Assuming no short id collisions, we'll then request each tx that we didn't find in either `vExtraTxnForCompact` or the mempool. \r\n\r\nI'm not sure how to fix this since compact block relay relies on this behavior. One possible way of fixing this was brought up here https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/27086#issuecomment-1426937832. ",
